# Customer Segmentation Using Unsupervised Learning

## Overview
This project focuses on customer segmentation using Machine Learning techniques. The main goal is to group customers based on their spending behavior and annual income so businesses can create better marketing strategies for each customer segment.

The project uses the Mall Customers Dataset and applies K-Means Clustering to identify different customer groups.

---

## Dataset
Dataset Used: Mall Customers Dataset

The dataset contains information such as:
- Customer ID
- Gender
- Age
- Annual Income
- Spending Score

---

## Technologies Used
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Scikit-learn

---

## Project Workflow
1. Loaded and explored the dataset
2. Performed Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
3. Selected important customer features
4. Applied K-Means Clustering
5. Used the Elbow Method to find the optimal number of clusters
6. Visualized customer clusters
7. Applied PCA for dimensionality reduction
8. Suggested marketing strategies for each customer segment

---

## Results
The model successfully divided customers into different groups based on spending habits and income levels. These insights can help businesses target customers more effectively with personalized marketing campaigns.

